  "plan": "## ProteomicsAnalysis GenePattern Module — Implementation Plan\n\n### 1. Overview\nProteomicsAnalysis is a GenePattern module that Runs the proteomics analysis on the set of input spectra\n\n### 2. Parameters\nThe module exposes 19 parameters:\n- Required: zip.filename, output.file, fill.na, normalize, peak.detection.method, filter.peaks, low.Da, high.Da, percentile, smoothing.size, adaptive.background.correction.strength, adaptive.background.correction.size, high.pass.filter.strength, high.pass.filter.factor\n- Optional: quality.threshold, filter.peaks.factor, peak.list.filename, random.seed, random.n.peaks\n\n### 3. Command Line\n```\n<R2.5> <libdir>pipeline.wrapper.R pipeline.wrapper <zip.filename> <output.file> <libdir> -_3<quality.threshold> -_40.00125 -_5<fill.na> -_6<normalize> -_7<peak.detection.method> -_8<filter.peaks> -_9<filter.peaks.factor> -10<peak.list.filename> -11<random.seed> -12<random.n.peaks> -13<low.Da> -14<high.Da> -15<percentile> -16<smoothing.size> -17<adaptive.background.correction.strength> -18<adaptive.background.correction.size> -19<high.pass.filter.strength> -20<high.pass.filter.factor>\n```\n\n### 4. Docker Image\nDocker image: \n\n### 5. Validation Strategy\n- Validate all required parameters are provided\n- Validate file formats match expected extensions\n- Check parameter value ranges where applicable\n\n### 6. Implementation Roadmap\nPhase 1: Wrapper script implementation\nPhase 2: Docker container setup\nPhase 3: Parameter validation and error handling\nPhase 4: Testing and documentation",
  "wrapper_script": "pipeline.wrapper.R",
  "command_line": "<R2.5> <libdir>pipeline.wrapper.R pipeline.wrapper <zip.filename> <output.file> <libdir> -_3<quality.threshold> -_40.00125 -_5<fill.na> -_6<normalize> -_7<peak.detection.method> -_8<filter.peaks> -_9<filter.peaks.factor> -10<peak.list.filename> -11<random.seed> -12<random.n.peaks> -13<low.Da> -14<high.Da> -15<percentile> -16<smoothing.size> -17<adaptive.background.correction.strength> -18<adaptive.background.correction.size> -19<high.pass.filter.strength> -20<high.pass.filter.factor>",
